features: Stay organized at school or at work with our 30 pack folders with prongs in assorted colors featuring 2 pockets and business card slots

Easily store and protect letter size paper documents and business cards in our standard plastic folders with clasps and pockets that measure 9.5” by 11.5” and are designed to hold standard 8.5” x 11” paper

Easily separate your important documents and assignments by projects using these 2 pocket portfolios with prongs that come in 6 distinct colors to help keep you organized at work or school, including 5 folders each of red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple
Use our durable 2 pocket poly plastic folders with prongs regularly without worry that they won’t last with our heavy-duty plastic construction that resists tearing and ripping
Ideal for any color coding system, our assorted color plastic folders make it easy to color code all your notes from class or work to help you easily organize by subject or project

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Get Organized Fast with our Multicolor 30 Pack of 2 Pocket Plastic Folders with Prongs Staying organized in today’s fast paced environment of school or work can seem like a tough challenge. By getting our 30 pack of heavy duty 2 pocket folders, you will be able to easily color code based on subject or project and add some vibrant colors to your organization routine. In addition to keeping you more organized, our plastic folders with 2 pockets will:

Stand up to the test of time with our heavy-duty plastic materialKeep important contact information on business cards organized with a card holder on each pocketProtect your important documents from wear and tear, stains, and even moisture as our folders are made from high quality waterproof plasticStore standard letter sized paper inside in the 3 hole punch prongs or pockets, as each folder measures 9.5” x 11.5”Brighten up your filing cabinet and help you color code your projects with 6 vibrant colors: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and purple

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great quality folders!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. These folders come in amazing colors, they are durable and built to last. I’m using them for a group project. It is exactly what I’m looking for and the price is right. Definitely a win!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Better than the ones in big box stores
reviews.reviewText: The plastic is all one piece and not too thin. The prongs are long enough to bind 200 pages of paper. Usually I shop the back to school sales in August and pick through the folders available in the big box stores. I will order these again to save time and money and get better quality!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2022
reviews.reviewText: I am a teacher and I needed folders for my students. I tried the ones at the store, but they fell apart within a month. These folders have fun colors and after months of use, still, look like new which says a lot.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Missing and defective
reviews.reviewText: One of thirty was missing, another was defective. 28 usable and seem to be of good quality.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 8, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I’m very pleased with the quality and also the fact they have two pockets.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great value for the cost
reviews.reviewText: Worked great for my student needs!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not bad if you don't mind them all being wavy
reviews.reviewText: There are too many shoved into a box too small so all of my folders have a wave to them. They would've been nice if they laid flat. I pride myself on providing my students with quality supplies and these look like I dug them out of the lost and found. Bummed because I need them for tomorrow so I guess I won't be returning them..

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 29, 2020
reviews.reviewText: I am excited to use these folders in my classroom. I am color coding my classroom to help me stay organized. These folders will help my students distinguish between one subject and another subject—for example red for math, purple for ELA. I will be ordering some more.
